WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:03.268
Does everybody know what time it is?

00:03.336 --> 00:05.099
<i>Tool Time!</i>

00:05.205 --> 00:09.767
That's right. Binford Tools is proud
to present Tim ''The Tool Man'' Taylor!

00:09.843 --> 00:12.141
[cheering]

00:13.980 --> 00:15.743
Thank you.

00:15.849 --> 00:17.180
Thank you, everybody.

00:18.118 --> 00:21.610
<i>Thank you, Heidi, our Tool Time
mother-to-be.</i>

00:21.688 --> 00:23.918
[cheering]

00:23.990 --> 00:26.857
<i>Welcome to Tool Time.
l am Tim ''The Tool Man'' Taylor.</i>

00:26.926 --> 00:29.793
Of course, you all know my assistant,
Al Borland.

00:29.863 --> 00:31.296
[cheering]

00:33.433 --> 00:36.334
Yesterday we showed you how to treat
an electrical burn.

00:41.141 --> 00:43.302
And a thermal burn.

00:44.911 --> 00:49.075
Now we're showing the important part,
fire safety equipment for the home.

00:49.149 --> 00:50.878
[siren sounding]

00:50.950 --> 00:54.613
The most important piece of equipment
in your home is the smoke alarm.

00:54.687 --> 00:57.155
We suggest putting one of these
in every room.

00:57.223 --> 01:00.454
And if you're like Tim
you should wear one on you belt.

01:05.331 --> 01:08.630
lt's also important to have
a quality chemical extinguisher.

01:08.701 --> 01:11.397
Right. Now, what if
your extinguisher is empty

01:11.471 --> 01:12.961
and the fire is spreading?

01:13.039 --> 01:15.530
Run like hell
and hope you have good insurance.

01:16.076 --> 01:18.135
Binford has a better idea.

01:18.211 --> 01:19.974
They always do, Al.

01:20.046 --> 01:21.809
Show us what they got.

01:21.881 --> 01:25.908
lntroducing the Binford 61 00
Home Fireman.

01:26.419 --> 01:28.478
lt taps right into your cold water line.

01:28.555 --> 01:32.389
You want to be sure the main valve
is in the ''o' position when stored.

01:32.459 --> 01:34.791
Now, you got 40 feet of hose,

01:34.861 --> 01:36.351
double hose construction

01:36.429 --> 01:38.659
<i>and a separate onloff switch right here.</i>

01:38.731 --> 01:40.062
- [man screaming]
- Oh!

01:43.970 --> 01:48.464
That's perfect if you want to put out
a cigarette or irritated Teamster.

01:51.211 --> 01:54.738
- But a real man needs real protection.
- What are you talking about?

01:54.814 --> 01:57.510
l remodeled a little more power
to the home fireman.

01:57.584 --> 02:02.078
- Uh, fire safety is no joking matter.
- l'm not joking about this, Al.

02:02.155 --> 02:04.783
Tim, this hose is not constructed
for any more pressure.

02:04.858 --> 02:07.349
l don't want to get wet.
The audience doesn't want to.

02:07.427 --> 02:11.363
Al! Ladies and gentlemen, the Tim Taylor
version of The Home Fireman.

02:11.431 --> 02:13.524
Ladies and gentlemen, take cover!

